{"TopicId":141432,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"IVAs with no windows or internal light source still letting outside light in","CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T09:08:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T09:08:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022how3fNB.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsAttachLink_image ipsAttachLink_left\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/how3fNB.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;float:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022GMBwFxT.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/GMBwFxT.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile working on some IVAs, I noticed that eventhough my IVAs have no windows or internal light sources*, for some reason the outside light seems to spill into the IVA regardless. I made sure that my main internal model and IVAs were all set to Layer 16 (Kerbals),\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/106805-nli2work/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022106805\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/106805-nli2work/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@nli2work\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78632-alexustas/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002278632\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/78632-alexustas/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@alexustas\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57380-cxg2827/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257380\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/57380-cxg2827/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@cxg2827\u003C/a\u003E and all IVA experts - any ideas what I might have missed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*I assume emissives don\u0027t count\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T09:21:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is actually an issue with all the IVAs 1.1. The external model does not cast a shadow on the interior. (It did in 1.0.5)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMade a bug report for the PreRelease and it was confirmed by\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/92433-porkjet/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002292433\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/92433-porkjet/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Porkjet\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(i think). Haven\u0027t found it though when looking through the tracker. So it might be fixed for the next update\u00A0or it\u00A0got lost in the transition to the offcial release.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT\u003C/strong\u003E: Strange, the bug report completely vanished, it is neither in the PreRelease nor in the release Tracker and isn\u0027t even listed in my recent activities there. I am 100% sure that the report existed,\u00A0one of the Devs even added some additional screenshots to show the issue and compare\u00A0with\u00A01.0.5.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT2\u003C/strong\u003E: Well, tracking the report back from my EMails i get this\u00A0nice message:\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(136,0,0);font-family:\u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.2px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,227,227);\u0022\u003EYou are not authorized to access this page.\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0Uhm, what?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-08T09:43:47Z\u0022 title=\u002206/08/2016 09:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T10:11:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222621910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465377688\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is actually an issue with all the IVAs 1.1. The external model does not cast a shadow on the interior. (It did in 1.0.5)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn hindsight, I just realized that my 1.0.5 IVAs did cast shadows as they were currently configured.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222621910\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465377688\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT\u003C/strong\u003E: Strange, the bug report completely vanished, it is neither in the PreRelease nor in the release Tracker and isn\u0027t even listed in my recent activities there. I am 100% sure that the report existed,\u00A0one of the Devs even added some additional screenshots to show the issue and compare\u00A0with\u00A01.0.5.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT2\u003C/strong\u003E: Well, tracking the report back from my EMails i get this\u00A0nice message:\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(136,0,0);font-family:\u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:13.2px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,227,227);\u0022\u003EYou are not authorized to access this page.\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0Uhm, what?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you could give me the ticket ID, I might be able to look it up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T10:14:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222621949\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465380702\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn hindsight, I just realized that my 1.0.5 IVAs did cast shadows as they were currently configured.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you could give me the ticket ID, I might be able to look it up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E it\u0027s been moved into internal Dev queue. Same happened to one of mine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-08T10:15:00Z\u0022 title=\u002206/08/2016 10:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by JPLRepo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T10:25:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222621949\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465380702\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn hindsight, I just realized that my 1.0.5 IVAs did cast shadows as they were currently configured.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you could give me the ticket ID, I might be able to look it up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ID of it is:\u00A0Bug #8439\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222621951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465380880\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E it\u0027s been moved into internal Dev queue. Same happened to one of mine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm, that explains it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-08T10:30:46Z\u0022 title=\u002206/08/2016 10:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-08T20:31:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the heads-up everyone - I\u0027m relieved to know that it\u0027s not a misconfiguration on my part, although it would be nice to have this fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the time being, I guess I\u0027ll test IVA interior lighting in orbit on the dark side of Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T05:21:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs a workaround \u00A0one can maybe add a mesh to the IVA that resembles the hull of the part and is not rendered but still casts shadows. Quite similar to the depthmask (actually when the depthmasks only lets you see throught the windws exactly like the depthmask). Maybe it is possible to force the mesh to cast shadows. Another idea would be to disable the backface culling of the interior if possible, so the IVA itself casts shadows inside.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaven\u0027t tried them yet, but will keep you updated when I did.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-09T05:24:35Z\u0022 title=\u002206/09/2016 05:24  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T07:36:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried out the suggestion(s)\u00A0and the first one works: The light only comes through the windows. Or actually in your case \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266272\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@sumghai\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0it wouldn\u0027t come in at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is the unity setup:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022JbkuGF6.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022436\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JbkuGF6.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA simple mesh with the KSP/Unlit Shader and the opacity set to 0. Cast Shadows for the Mesh Renderer should be on by default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENote \u003C/strong\u003Ethat the faces of this mesh should face to the outside.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisabling the backface culling prooved to be less easy. One would have to deactivate it in the shaders (while compiling them when i correctly understood the documentation of unity). This would also look ugly\u00A0with the cutaway feature and is therefore not really an option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/92433-porkjet/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002292433\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/92433-porkjet/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Porkjet\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0might this also be a possible (easy) fix for the stock IVAs?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-09T07:46:57Z\u0022 title=\u002206/09/2016 07:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T07:41:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222623462\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465457809\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried out the suggestion(s)\u00A0and the first one works: The light only comes through the windows. Or actually in your case \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266272\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@sumghai\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0it wouldn\u0027t come in at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is the unity setup:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JbkuGF6.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022JbkuGF6.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022436\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/JbkuGF6.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA simple mesh with the KSP/Unlit Shader and the opacity set to 0. Cast Shadows for the Mesh Renderer should be on by default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENote \u003C/strong\u003Ethat the faces of this mesh should face to the outside.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try out technique number one later tonight, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T07:50:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis should probably go to whoever has that issue of Nils277 assigned to them. Not sure who? \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/92433-porkjet/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002292433\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/92433-porkjet/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Porkjet\u003C/a\u003E or \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E or someone might be able to pass it on?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nMy thoughts here are that given Internal space and external space (Scaled space) are orientated differently.. when you render the IVA camera the way it is now being done in 1.1\u002B I can\u0027t see how you would ever see the shadows of the external part model fall onto the internal model. Given they are in two different location/orientations.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThat is assuming the two cameras being used to render both the internal space and external space have the Sun (light source) orientated appropriately for each...\u003Cbr\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t the only way to get the external model / mesh shadow to fall on the internal one would be they are located in the same position and orientation? Or you copy them and put the copy in the right location / orientation?\u003Cbr\u003E\nOr do as Nils277 has suggested and put a copy of the external into the internal model to cast the shadows (just another way of doing the copy or move in real time). Only this way would probably be cheaper.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T08:10:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA small brainstorming with JLPRepo\u00A0revealed some even easier ways this could be fixed by Squad:\u00A0Either also rendering the already added DepthMasks for the Cutaway in the depthmap for the Shadowmaps (given that it only has holes for the windows) or add a shader that is only rendered for the Shadowmaps but not in the actual rendering scene, which might have an even smaller impact on the performance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-09T08:11:30Z\u0022 title=\u002206/09/2016 08:11  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T08:21:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EExperimentation with \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122414\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nils277\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s workaround\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMixed results I\u0027m afraid:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uMeBCpG.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;\u0022 alt=\u0022uMeBCpG.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Portrait camera still appears to be brightly lit on the outside, while the Internal itself in both overlay and IVA views is casting some shadows - but not 100%, as I\u0027m still seeing stray beams of light even though there are no actual windows.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sX7iBci.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;\u0022 alt=\u0022sX7iBci.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nZooming with the mouse wheel shows another problem - it seems that the unlit shader interferes with the Depth Mask clipping, such that some internal props are masked when they should not be masked (e.g. the locker props for the internal racks).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ujDhumo.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;\u0022 alt=\u0022ujDhumo.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I\u0027ll put this aside for the time being.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThe case of the \u0022missing\u0022 bugtracker ticket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E has informed me that the issue has been moved to the internal tracker, but no confirmation as to whether it\u0027s actually being worked on, or whether the fix will be implemented in 1.1.3 or 1.2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T08:38:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222623496\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465460486\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EExperimentation with \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122414\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Nils277\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s workaround\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMixed results I\u0027m afraid:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uMeBCpG.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uMeBCpG.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/uMeBCpG.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Portrait camera still appears to be brightly lit on the outside, while the Internal itself in both overlay and IVA views is casting some shadows - but not 100%, as I\u0027m still seeing stray beams of light even though there are no actual windows.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sX7iBci.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sX7iBci.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sX7iBci.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nZooming with the mouse wheel shows another problem - it seems that the unlit shader interferes with the Depth Mask clipping, such that some internal props are masked when they should not be masked (e.g. the locker props for the internal racks).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ujDhumo.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ujDhumo.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ujDhumo.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:280px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I\u0027ll put this aside for the time being.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThe case of the \u0022missing\u0022 bugtracker ticket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E has informed me that the issue has been moved to the internal tracker, but no confirmation as to whether it\u0027s actually being worked on, or whether the fix will be implemented in 1.1.3 or 1.2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, i have not recognized that Kerbals in the Portraits are not affected by this. :-/\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you used a simplified mesh for the shadows or the original external model? Might be that some details of the external model are too small to be taken into account by the shadowmap.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the problem with the masked Props appears because the mesh that casts the shadwos is\u00A0rendered but with full transparency. All meshes that have also transparency are not rendered when they are behind other meshes with transparency (except the cutoff transparency). This could only be fixed by not rendering the mesh that casts the shadwos in the normal scene at all.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the info on the tracker \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-09T08:38:51Z\u0022 title=\u002206/09/2016 08:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 9, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T08:47:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222623511\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465461491\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave you used a simplified mesh for the shadows or the original external model? Might be that some details of the external model are too small to be taken into account by the shadowmap.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used a simplified mesh, a 24-sided cylinder with triangular fan ends.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T09:15:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222623521\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465462074\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used a simplified mesh, a 24-sided cylinder with triangular fan ends.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm...weird, don\u0027t know why this is happening then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mesh casts shadows in the Kerbals in the Portrait though. Maybe you use layer 20? With layer 16 it works.\u003Cbr\u003E\nBit i can confirm that the transparent mesh does some really weird things when the cutaway is enabled. Had one\u00A0Kerbal where the head was invisible and only the eyes and teeth were visible...creepy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-09T09:25:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222623541\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221465463752\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe you use layer 20? With layer 16 it works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt made no noticeable difference for me whether I used Layer 16 or 20, unfortunately.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuess we\u0027ll have to wait until 1.1.3 or 1.2, then.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-10T00:28:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnvm. you already do it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-06-10T00:29:18Z\u0022 title=\u002206/10/2016 12:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJune 10, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by nli2work\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"InsaneDruid","CreatedById":137849,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T17:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill not fixed, or is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T21:04:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645690\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466790796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137849\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022InsaneDruid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, InsaneDruid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill not fixed, or is it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs of 1.1.3, the issue appears to have been (mostly) resolved:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/15543-mu/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002215543\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/15543-mu/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mu\u003C/a\u003E set it so that internal models (not props) now render double-sided shadows\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Most of the stock pods IVAs look better now, but there are occasional bit of stray lights leaking through gaps. \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E and I suspect that to be issues with individual internal models.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- I revisited my airlock model just now, fewer stray lights leaking in now. Might need to tweak my prop positioning and internal model mesh a bit more, however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T21:22:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmight help to have some mesh overlap where you are getting leaks. Edges that meet up exactly tend to leak light because\u00A0shadow map resolution isn\u0027t high enough.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-06-24T21:41:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222645994\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466803378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106805\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nli2work\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, nli2work said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmight help to have some mesh overlap where you are getting leaks. Edges that meet up exactly tend to leak light because\u00A0shadow map resolution isn\u0027t high enough.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspected that to be the case. Will do, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-05T10:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222646016\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221466804514\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sumghai\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 25/06/2016 at 7:41 AM, sumghai said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspected that to be the case. Will do, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266272\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sumghai\u003C/a\u003E, curious to know how you went?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-05T20:24:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222662009\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022141432\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221467714105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266272\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@sumghai\u003C/a\u003E, curious to know how you went?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hadn\u0027t had time to revisit this just yet I\u0027m afraid, been busy with a major project at work and updating SDHI SMS for 1.1.3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll let you know how I get on later this month.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sumghai","CreatedById":66272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-22T22:37:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122414\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nils277\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve resumed work on FusTek after a hiatus, and despite going back and trying \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122414\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122414-nils277/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nils277\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s idea I still can\u0027t seem to get the IVA to cast shadows properly - it\u0027s not just sharp edges leaking light in, but entire faces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m currently redoing my IVAs from scratch, experimenting with meshes, normals and shaders. I\u0027m also re-examining \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78632-alexustas/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002278632\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78632-alexustas/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@alexustas\u003C/a\u003E\u0027 ALCOR Pod IVA, since I recall it used to successfully implement IVA shadows, and I want to see how it was implemented / if it had been affected by the 1.2.x updates.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the meantime, if you guys have advice or sample models I can try, that\u0027d be greatly appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: ALCOR hasn\u0027t been updated since KSP 1.0.4, and while Alex is working on a fix, the shutters on the latest version don\u0027t seem to work, so I can\u0027t confirm whether the ALCOR IVA can cast internal shadows properly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-23T11:45:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266272\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66272-sumghai/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sumghai\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhere is a Unity Package with one of my most recent IVAs: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/wplqdvwdew7wt0o/CrewCabin.unitypackage\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECrewCabin.unitypackage.\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt contains the model as Blender File. The shadows are cast correctly from it. Hope this helps.\u003Cbr\u003E\nBtw, i\u00A0get rid of the leaking edges by having an additional mesh without any sharp egdes (in blender). When set to the right shader (KSP/Alpha/Unlit/Transparent) it does not cause\u00A0any interference with stock cutout or portraits. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdit:\u003C/strong\u003E If this does not help, could you upload one of your problematic models? Maybe we find something fishy in it that causes your problem \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-23T14:38:46Z\u0022 title=\u002211/23/2016 02:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 23, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}